observations.recommendation:
In light of the foregoing, we recommended and Management is agreeable to:
Assign responsibility to the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator (MPDC) for the planning, monitoring, and evaluation of all programs, projects, and activities funded by the 20% Development Fund (20% DF). Ensure that development projects are well-planned and procurement-and-implementation-ready;
Stop the practice of transferring funds to other bank accounts or barangays, and reporting these transfers as utilization and accomplishment. Instruct the Municipal Budget Officer to accurately report the actual utilization of the 20% DF.
If the transfer of funds to barangays is unavoidable, amend the terms specified in the Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) and require the Municipal Accountant to review and sign as witness to the agreement;
Instruct the MPDC and Municipal Engineer to coordinate with the barangays to identify completed projects and ensure that all necessary documentation is submitted to the Accounting Unit for proper liquidation and recording. For projects that are yet to be implemented, require the Barangays to immediately return the unutilized funds to the LGU; and
Instruct the Municipal Budget Officer and the MPDC to examine the actual utilization of the 20% Development Fund from 2017 to the present, and identify any savings or unutilized funds and reallocate these resources to other essential development projects.

We recommended and it was agreed by Management to:
Stop utilizing the Special Trust Fund for the unspent LDRRMF of the previous years without a duly approved AIP from the local Sanggunian and the Local Chief Executive (LCE);
Strictly adhere to Section 6.5 of the NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01 and Section of 5.1.2 COA Circular No.  2021-002;
Require the LDRRMC to identify and propose projects, programs, and activities (PPAs) to be funded from the LDRRMF Special Trust Fund, and ensure these PPAs are incorporated as a separate caption in the LGU’s LDRRMFIP, subject to approval by the Sanggunian and the Municipal Mayor, in line with Section 6.5 of the NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01; and
Regularly monitor the balances of the STF and revert back to the General Fund after five (5) years, to be allocated for social services, in accordance with NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01.

We recommended that Management finish its annual physical count of its property, plant and equipment and submit a copy of the same to COA on or before January 31 of each year;
We also recommended that Management reconcile its PPE Subsidiary Ledgers and its property cards regularly, if needed; and
Further, we ardently recommended that Management prioritize / commit to undertake the cleansing of PPE account balance pursuant to COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020.

We recommended that Management:
Require the Municipal Development Council and the budget committee to judiciously plan and identify the Programs/Projects/Activities (PPAs) to be funded out of the 20% Development Fund and include only those that are feasible and could be accomplished within the target date of completion;
Fully implement the programmed development PPAs during the year as embodied in the Annual Investment/Development Plan and ensure optimum utilization of the 20% Development Fund for the benefit of the constituents of the Municipality;
Strictly observe proper timelines and install effective monitoring of fund utilization and implementation; and
Ensure that all savings from completed projects and all projects that are no longer feasible and not yet implemented are considered for immediate realignment subject to budgetary rules or reverted back to the unappropriated surplus of the 20% Development Fund for re-appropriation to other development projects.

We recommended that Management:
Stop utilizing the Special Trust Fund for the unspent LDRRMF of the previous years without a duly approved AIP by the local Sanggunian and the LCE;
Strictly adhere to Section 6.5 of the NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01 and Section of 5.1.2 COA Circular No.  2021-002;
Require the LDRRMC to identify projects, programs, and activities to be funded from the LDRRMF Special Trust Fund and incorporate these PPAs as a separate caption of the LGU’s LDRRMFIP subject to the approval by the Sanggunian and the Municipal Mayor pursuant to Section 6.5 of the NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01; and
Regularly monitor the balances of the STF and revert back to the General Fund any unutilized amount after five (5) years which will be used fund for social services NDRRMC-DBM-DILG Joint Circular No. 2013-01.
